  "title": "Kirchhoff junction - is X or Y at higher potential",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two parallel vertical portions of a circuit with a resistor. A horizontal branch links the two vertical circuit portions. It intersects the left vertical circuit portion at point X and intersects the right vertical circuit portion at point Y. The horizontal branch has the resistor. From top to bottom, above point Y the right vertical circuit portion has a current indicated of 2 amps directed vertically downward, and below point Y the right vertical circuit portion has a current indicated of 12 amps directed vertically downward.\" src=\"/images/71cc8985c729af6d16180700c6ce3e86.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows a portion of a circuit that includes a resistor. The currents in two of the wire segments are indicated. Which of the two labeled positions is at a higher potential, and what evidence or reasoning supports the claim?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>. The current in the resistor is directed toward the right.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>. The wires at this junction all have currents directed away from point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>. The current in the resistor is toward the left.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>. The wires at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> all have currents directed into point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
